tournament.name: APIIT Law School Inter-School Debate Competition

feedback.answer:
Shakeeb demonstrated exceptional professionalism, impartiality, and expertise throughout the debate proceedings. Their insightful feedback, thorough evaluation of arguments, and fair judgment greatly enhanced the quality of the competition and ensured a rewarding experience for all participants.
Their dedication to upholding the standards of debate and providing constructive criticism reflects positively on the integrity of our event. I am truly grateful for Shakeeb's valuable contributions and commend them for their commitment to excellence.
Please convey our sincerest thanks to the above adjudicator on behalf of all the participants. Their exemplary adjudication played a pivotal role in the success of the debate, and I look forward to the opportunity to collaborate with them again in the future.

Adjudicator seemed somewhat drowsy, and zoned off a couple times during the end of the debate and during feedback. This may be due to how late at night it was. Also the clash identification was not as clear cut we we'd prefer.

thankyou so much for your time and thoughts aiya. gave honest feedback. pointed out not only the flaws but also the good things. Engaging feedback as both me and my team member(we were iron personing) were feeling good because of how stressful iron personing is. thankyou aiya
We didn't have an adj cz we got swing team.
thankyou for the judgement. helpful to improve ourselves throughout the session entirely. got some feedbacks personally and team wise and it actually helps us improve. thankyou so much

feedback you gave to our team was very honest. helped me out to do well in the next debate. didn't just point out the flaws but also the good things we had and it did not make me nor my members feel demotivated. thankyou so much for your time and thoughts akki
The adjudication was okay but not clear.
Good constructive personal feedback as well as case feedback
It was slightly biased in our opinion

It was one of the best adjudications we ever received. The adj was really elaborative and gave detailed individual feedback. We highly appreciate the clash analysis. We noticed how he had been extremely attentive to minute details and had great clarity in adjudication.

The adj's feedback was quite clear and nicely elaborated. We appreciate how she had her video on throughout the debate. But we didn't expect the feed back she had that module was not necessary for prop in a THW motion. Either way, she was nice.
We appreciate the adj having the video turned on and his feedback was nice too.

tournament.motion: This house would prohibit the dismissal of employees for their use of free speech or expression outside the workplace (e.g. on social media)
This house prefers a world in which religions do not encourage self-deprivation (e.g., ritual fasting, asceticism, voluntary poverty)

This house believes that animal advocacy groups should emphasize environmental concerns that arise from animal exploitation (e.g. deforestation in order to have land to house/feed cattle, the carbon footprint of producing meat) over the suffering of animals

This house would give unions a veto over political appointments made in their field of work (e.g. bus drivers/taxi drivers unions when appointing Transport Minister, teachers unions when appointing an Education Minister)

This house believes that the targeting of human shields in war should be legal. A human shield is a civilian or group of civilians who are forced to shield a legitimate military target in order to prevent the enemy from attacking it.
This house, as a child of a financially stable Sri Lankan family, would prefer be an only child than the middle sibling of three

A technology exists to quantify/measure one's partner's love for them. 0% shows that there is no love at all while 100% shows the utmost sincere and loyal love. TH, as a person in a long and committed relationship, would use the technology
The Golden Rule states "do unto others as you would have them do unto you" This house opposes the widespread belief of the golden rule

THW replace direct state funding of arts with the regular distribution of culture vouchers A culture voucher is a token that can be reimbursed for various cultural activities (e.g. theatre tickets, gallery entrance fees etc.) up to a fixed monetary value. At the point of the use, the state pays the relevant cost of the cultural activity for which the voucher was reimbursed. These tokens are currently issued in France and are in the works in Germany.
